♪ I'LL BE READY

00:57.231 --> 00:59.798
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

00:59.929 --> 01:02.932
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:21.081 --> 01:22.908
♪ CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:23.039 --> 01:26.477
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:29.480 --> 01:33.397
♪ [I'LL BE READY]
I'LL BE READY ♪

01:33.528 --> 01:35.312
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

01:35.443 --> 01:37.314
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.445 --> 01:40.622
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.752 --> 01:43.407
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.016 --> 01:46.976
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:59.728 --> 02:01.469
-MAN: LAST TIME
ON BAYWATCH.

02:01.599 --> 02:03.166
WELL, THE TRADITION CONTINUES.

02:03.297 --> 02:06.778
FIRST NEELY,
THEN DONNA, NOW LANI.

02:06.909 --> 02:08.606
ALL ON THE COVER
OF INSIDE SPORTS.

02:08.737 --> 02:10.826
-NOW HE'S TAKIN'
THEM TO ALASKA.

02:10.955 --> 02:12.741
-I FINALLY TRACKED DOWN PETER,

02:12.871 --> 02:14.786
HE'S LIVING IN JUNEAU.

02:14.917 --> 02:16.484
ONE OF THE STOPS ON THE CRUISE.

02:16.614 --> 02:18.747
-SO, YOU'RE GOING TO
INTRODUCE ASHLEY TO HER DADDY.

02:18.877 --> 02:20.792
-CONGRATULATIONS,
YOU'RE THE WINNER

02:20.923 --> 02:23.752
OF THE PRINCESS CRUISES
ALASKAN AIRLINE SWEEPSTAKES,

02:23.882 --> 02:25.493
I'M GOIN' TO ALASKA.

02:26.276 --> 02:27.712
-YOU CAN CUT
THOUSANDS OF STONES

02:27.843 --> 02:29.497
FROM JUST ONE OF THESE EMERALDS.

02:29.627 --> 02:31.803
WE RISKED OUR LIVES
DIVING FOR THESE.

02:31.934 --> 02:33.718
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKIN' ABOUT?

02:33.849 --> 02:35.503
-I'M TALKIN' ABOUT
GETTING OUR FAIR SHARE
OF THE PROFITS.

02:35.633 --> 02:36.939
-YOU FORGETTIN' WHO
WE'RE DEALING WITH, HERE?

02:37.069 --> 02:38.288
LOOK, THESE GUYS ARE KILLERS.

02:38.419 --> 02:39.768
THEY KILL TO GET THESE EMERALDS,

02:39.898 --> 02:40.725
THEY'LL KILL TO KEEP 'EM.

02:50.039 --> 02:51.388
-I DON'T KNOW,

02:51.519 --> 02:52.520
BUT I THINK
WE'VE BEEN DOUBLE CROSSED.

02:52.650 --> 02:53.956
-REMEMBER WHAT SHE LOOKS LIKE?

02:54.086 --> 02:55.175
BLOND HAIR, BLUE EYES,

02:55.305 --> 02:56.654
THE PERFECT GIRL NEXT DOOR.

02:56.785 --> 02:57.699
-I'M CLAIR HODGES NOW,

02:57.829 --> 02:59.091
I'M A REDHEAD.

02:59.831 --> 03:01.398
WE MAY HAVE A PROBLEM HERE.

03:01.529 --> 03:03.487
QUIN'S BODY'S FLOATED
TO THE SURFACE.

03:03.618 --> 03:04.706
-STOP THE BOAT.

03:06.664 --> 03:08.666
-THE LIFEGUARDS HAVE
ALREADY SPOTTED IT.

03:08.797 --> 03:11.103
I CAN'T TELL
IF HE'S DEAD OR ALIVE.

03:22.027 --> 03:22.898
-ARE YOU OKAY?

03:23.028 --> 03:24.247
-I'M NOT SURE.

03:24.378 --> 03:25.770
-SO, YOU GUYS
GOIN' OUT OR WHAT?

03:25.901 --> 03:27.468
-ACTUALLY, I'M GONNA
TAKE HER ON THE CRUISE.

03:27.598 --> 03:29.905
-YOU'RE GONNA TAKE
A GIRL YOU JUST MET

03:30.035 --> 03:31.559
ON AN EIGHT DAY, ALASKAN CRUISE?

03:31.689 --> 03:32.647
-SHE'S A NICE GIRL,

03:32.777 --> 03:34.214
I WANNA HELP HER OUT.

03:34.344 --> 03:36.433
-YOU SHOULD'VE LISTENED TO ME,
YOU BASTARD.

03:36.564 --> 03:39.610
GREED IS GOOD. BYE, BYE BABY.

03:39.741 --> 03:41.395
-LISTEN, I WANT
THOSE EMERALDS BACK.

03:41.525 --> 03:44.093
I DON'T EVER WANT TO SEE
MISS LESLIE STRYKER AGAIN, EVER.

03:44.224 --> 03:45.573
-I GUARANTEE YOU,

03:45.703 --> 03:47.836
SHE WILL NEVER GET OFF
THAT CRUISE SHIP ALIVE.

05:44.779 --> 05:45.606
-AWESOME, RIGHT?

05:45.736 --> 05:46.824
-YEP.

05:46.955 --> 05:48.217
EVER BEEN ON A CRUISE BEFORE?

05:48.348 --> 05:49.131
-NO, YOU?

05:49.261 --> 05:50.132
-YEAH, ONCE.

05:50.262 --> 05:51.829
-HOW WAS IT?

05:51.960 --> 05:54.049
-PRETTY AWESOME UNTIL
STEPHANIE FELL OVERBOARD,

05:54.179 --> 05:55.920
ENDING UP JUMPING IN AFTER HER.

05:56.051 --> 05:57.226
-YOU KIDDIN' ME.
WHAT HAPPENED?

05:57.357 --> 05:58.923
-NEVER HEARD THAT STORY?

05:59.054 --> 06:00.490
-NO, BUT I HAVE A FEELING
YOU'RE GONNA TELL ME.

06:00.621 --> 06:02.449
-STEP INTO MY OFFICE,
I'LL BUY YOU A BEER.

06:02.579 --> 06:04.451
COUPLE MORE CERVEZAS, PLEASE.

06:04.581 --> 06:05.669
-RIGHT AWAY, SIR.

06:06.714 --> 06:08.280
-SO ANYWAY,

06:08.411 --> 06:10.631
HERE WE ARE, CRUISING
DOWN THE MEXICAN RIVIERA.

06:10.761 --> 06:12.807
I LOOK OUT THE WINDOW,
THROUGH THE PORTHOLE.

06:12.937 --> 06:14.112
-STEPHANIE
-OH, OH.

06:14.243 --> 06:15.157
RED ALERT, THERE'S NEELY.

06:16.245 --> 06:17.507
HERE GOES THE BIG SURPRISE.

06:17.638 --> 06:19.117
-QUICK, FOLLOW ME.
FOLLOW ME.

06:31.086 --> 06:32.043
[WHISTLING]

06:32.174 --> 06:34.655
HEY, HEY, DOWN, DOWN HERE.

06:37.788 --> 06:39.442
THANKS, PUT 'EM ON MY ROOM.

06:39.573 --> 06:40.356
-SURE?

06:40.487 --> 06:41.270
-IT'S ON ME.

06:41.401 --> 06:42.489
ANYWAY,

06:43.054 --> 06:44.012
THERE I WAS...

06:52.716 --> 06:53.761
-HEY, WHAT'S UP?

06:53.891 --> 06:55.589
-NOTHING MUCH.

06:55.719 --> 06:56.459
-YOU SEEN THE GIRLS AROUND?
-NO, I'VE BEEN LAYING LOW,

06:56.590 --> 06:57.852
I HAVEN'T SEEN 'EM.

06:57.982 --> 06:59.419
-COOL, DON'T WANNA SPOIL
THE SURPRISE.

07:01.725 --> 07:02.857
SO, HOW'S YOUR FRIEND DOIN'?

07:02.987 --> 07:04.511
-REALLY GOOD.

07:04.641 --> 07:06.121
YOU KNOW, ACTUALLY, SHE'S
A REALLY COOL CHICK.

07:06.251 --> 07:07.905
I DON'T KNOW WHY MY DAD'S
SO BENT OUTTA SHAPE.

07:08.036 --> 07:09.907
-MY DAD WAS
THE SAME WAY WITH ME.

07:10.038 --> 07:12.083
THEY ALWAYS THINK
THEY KNOW WHAT'S BEST FOR YOU.

07:12.214 --> 07:14.042
IT'LL BE THE SAME WAY
WHEN YOU HAVE A KID.

07:18.873 --> 07:19.656
-HEY BUD.

07:19.787 --> 07:20.657
-WHAT'S HAPPENIN', MAN?

07:20.788 --> 07:21.571
-[MUFFLED SPEECH]

07:21.702 --> 07:22.572
-HEY.

07:22.703 --> 07:23.573
-WHATCHA DOIN'?

07:24.574 --> 07:25.967
-BUYING CLAIR A DRESS.

07:26.750 --> 07:27.664
-WHAT?

07:27.795 --> 07:29.361
-HEY, ITS MY MONEY, RIGHT?

07:29.492 --> 07:30.101
I CAN DO WHAT I WANT WITH IT.
-THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

07:30.232 --> 07:31.451
-THE POINT IS,

07:31.581 --> 07:33.148
YOU'RE STILL TRYING
TO RUN MY LIFE.

07:33.278 --> 07:36.064
WHY DON'T YOU JUST LET
ME ENJOY MY CRUISE?

07:38.501 --> 07:39.589
-YOU WERE TALKIN' TO HIM?

07:46.422 --> 07:48.032
-THIS PLACE IS AMAZING.

07:48.163 --> 07:49.599
-LADIES, GOOD EVENING.

07:49.730 --> 07:51.035
WELCOME TO VENETIAN DINING ROOM.
-HI.

07:51.166 --> 07:52.863
-YOU LOOK SO WONDERFUL.

07:52.994 --> 07:53.908
-THANK YOU.

07:54.038 --> 07:55.562
-THIS IS A BEAUTIFUL ROOM.

07:55.692 --> 07:57.564
-BEAUTIFUL, I WILL LEAVE
THE SPECIAL TABLE FOR YOU.

07:57.694 --> 07:58.652
LET'S GO.

07:58.782 --> 08:00.001
-OH, YEAH.
-ALRIGHT.

08:05.528 --> 08:07.138
-CHECK THIS OUT.

08:09.184 --> 08:11.099
WELL, I WONDER WHAT
JD. AND NEELY ARE DOING

08:11.229 --> 08:12.535
RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

08:12.666 --> 08:13.971
NEELY'S PROBABLY
GETTIN' A HAIR CUT.

08:15.146 --> 08:16.104
-YOU SEE 'EM?

08:16.844 --> 08:17.714
-RIGHT THERE, RIGHT THERE.

08:20.369 --> 08:21.718
-BUON APPETITO!

08:22.414 --> 08:23.372
-EXCUSE ME, SIR.

08:23.503 --> 08:24.852
-GOOD DAY, MAY I HELP YOU?

08:27.245 --> 08:29.987
-ACTUALLY, I'M GONNA START WITH
THE SHRIMP COCKTAIL,

08:30.118 --> 08:31.293
AND THEN I'M GONNA
HAVE THE CAESAR SALAD.

08:31.423 --> 08:33.207
-BUONGIORNO, DARLING.

08:33.337 --> 08:34.208
I WAS WONDERING IF YOU'D LIKE
TO HAVE A LOOK AT THE WINE.

08:34.339 --> 08:35.732
-MITCH.

08:35.863 --> 08:37.125
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

08:37.255 --> 08:38.953
-PERHAPS YOU'D PREFER
SOME CHAMPAGNE?

08:39.082 --> 08:40.432
-CODY!

08:40.563 --> 08:41.520
-WHAT'S HAPPENING?
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:43.217 --> 08:44.393
HOW'D YOU GUYS GET ON BOARD?

08:44.524 --> 08:45.655
-WE STOWED AWAY.

08:46.177 --> 08:47.265
-ITS GREAT TO SEE YOU.

08:47.396 --> 08:48.702
-I MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

08:48.832 --> 08:50.268
-YEAH, ME TOO.
YOU GUYS LOOK GREAT.

08:50.399 --> 08:51.792
-SERIOUSLY, HOW'D
YOU GUYS GET HERE?

08:51.922 --> 08:53.750
-THERE WAS A CONTEST PUT
ON BY PRINCESS CRUISES

08:53.881 --> 08:56.187
AND ALASKA AIRLINES,
HOBIE ENTERED THE CONTEST,

08:56.318 --> 08:58.059
HOBIE WON THE CONTEST,

08:58.189 --> 09:01.366
AND THE FIRST PRIZE WAS FOUR
TICKETS ON THE PRINCESS CRUISES.

09:01.497 --> 09:02.542
-WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

09:02.672 --> 09:04.152
-AND MISS THAT
LOOK ON YOUR FACE?

09:04.282 --> 09:05.588
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

09:05.719 --> 09:06.676
WHERE'S ASHLEY?

09:06.807 --> 09:07.547
-OH, SHE'S BACK AT THE ROOM.

09:07.677 --> 09:08.548
WE HAVE A SITTER.

09:09.331 --> 09:10.462
-I THOUGHT SHE MIGHT
BE NEEDING THESE.

09:10.593 --> 09:11.681
-DIAPERS?

09:12.377 --> 09:13.378
THAT'S SO SWEET.

09:13.509 --> 09:14.728
-COME ON YOU GUYS, SIT DOWN.

09:14.858 --> 09:15.946
-YEAH, LET'S POP THIS BABY.

09:16.077 --> 09:16.904
-WOO.

09:17.034 --> 09:18.166
-YEAH, LET'S DO IT.

09:18.296 --> 09:19.167
[CORK POP]

09:19.297 --> 09:21.561
[YELLING AND CHEERING]

09:21.691 --> 09:22.910
-TABLE FOR TWO, PLEASE.

09:23.040 --> 09:24.476
-THIS WAY, FOLLOW ME, PLEASE.

09:25.913 --> 09:27.044
-HEY, WHERE'S DONNA?

09:27.175 --> 09:28.219
-SHE WASN'T HUNGRY.

09:28.350 --> 09:29.569
TOO BUSY LOOKIN' FOR LOVE.

09:29.699 --> 09:31.353
-WELL, IT IS THE LOVE BOAT.

09:31.483 --> 09:32.484
-OH, THERE'S HOBIE.

09:32.615 --> 09:34.095
COME ON, COME OVER HERE.

09:34.225 --> 09:35.923
-WHO'S THIS GIRL HE'S WITH?

09:36.053 --> 09:37.359
-I DON'T KNOW, HE BROUGHT
HER ON THE CRUISE WITH HIM.

09:37.489 --> 09:39.056
-YOU'RE KIDDING.
-I WISH.

09:39.187 --> 09:40.754
-ISN'T SHE A
LITTLE OLD FOR HIM?

09:40.884 --> 09:42.886
-I'M GLAD I'M NOT THE
ONLY ONE WHO NOTICED THAT.

09:44.714 --> 09:46.673
-HOBIE, THANK YOU SO MUCH.

09:46.803 --> 09:48.631
OH, WINNING THIS CONTEST.

09:48.762 --> 09:49.937
-I'M GLAD TO BRING YA.

09:50.067 --> 09:51.808
-COME ON, COME ON, COME ON OVER.

09:51.939 --> 09:54.376
-NEELY, LANI,
THIS IS CLAIR HODGES.

09:54.506 --> 09:56.291
-HI.
-HI, NICE TO MEET YOU.

09:56.421 --> 09:57.553
-HI.
-HELLO.

09:57.684 --> 09:58.641
-HI.
-HI.

09:58.772 --> 09:59.729
-HAVE A NICE DINNER.

09:59.860 --> 10:00.904
-AREN'T YOU GUYS GONNA JOIN US?

10:01.557 --> 10:02.950
-NO, THAT'S OKAY.

10:03.080 --> 10:04.865
WE KNOW WHEN WE'RE NOT WANTED.

10:06.606 --> 10:07.824
COME ON.

10:25.276 --> 10:26.364
-SORRY.

10:32.153 --> 10:33.241
-HEY.

10:33.371 --> 10:34.634
-CODY.

10:34.764 --> 10:36.157
WHAT'RE YOU DOING HERE?

10:36.287 --> 10:37.724
-ITS A LONG STORY.

10:37.854 --> 10:39.682
-CAME WITH MITCH, HOBIE,
AND HOBIE'S GIRLFRIEND.

10:39.813 --> 10:40.814
-HOBIE'S GIRLFRIEND?

10:40.944 --> 10:42.467
-THAT'S AN EVEN LONGER STORY.

10:42.598 --> 10:44.556
-YEAH, I'LL FILL YOU IN
ON ALL THE DETAILS LATER.

10:44.687 --> 10:46.863
IN THE MEANTIME,
WHAT'S UP WITH YOU AND MR. LIMO?

10:47.516 --> 10:48.735
-I HAVEN'T BEEN
ABLE TO FIND HIM.

10:48.865 --> 10:50.301
AND BELIEVE ME, I'VE TRIED.

10:50.432 --> 10:51.999
I'VE WALKED EVERY DECK
ON THE SHIP.

10:52.129 --> 10:53.478
-WELL, ITS ONLY
THE FIRST NIGHT.

10:53.609 --> 10:54.741
HE'S BOUND TO TURN UP
SOONER OR LATER.

11:00.224 --> 11:02.662
-MAN: MID 20S,
BROWN EYES, BLONDE HAIR,

11:02.792 --> 11:04.794
PERFECT GIRL NEXT DOOR.

11:08.885 --> 11:10.626
-HELLO, LESLIE.

11:12.236 --> 11:14.717
IRONIC THAT WE SHOULD MEET ON
THE AIR BOLD DECK, ISN'T IT?

11:14.848 --> 11:16.545
-I BEG YOUR PARDON?

11:16.676 --> 11:18.373
-I BELIEVE THAT YOU HAVE
SOMETHING THAT BELONGS TO ME.

11:18.503 --> 11:19.940
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

11:20.070 --> 11:21.115
-I'M REALLY NOT IN THE MOOD FOR

11:21.245 --> 11:22.290
-EXCUSE ME.

11:22.420 --> 11:23.378
THAT'S MY CHAIR.

11:23.987 --> 11:25.162
AND THAT'S MY WIFE.

11:26.381 --> 11:29.036
-I AM TERRIBLY SORRY.

11:29.166 --> 11:30.951
I THOUGHT YOU WERE SOMEONE ELSE.

11:37.000 --> 11:37.914
-WISH ME LUCK.
-GOOD LUCK.

11:38.045 --> 11:39.263
-NO MORE BETS, THANK YOU.

11:44.312 --> 11:45.574
BLACK EIGHT.

11:51.580 --> 11:52.842
-ALRIGHT, THIS IS
MY LAST DOLLAR.

11:52.973 --> 11:54.365
NOW, YOU GOTTA WIN

11:54.496 --> 11:55.192
OR I'M GONNA HAVE TO
BORROW MONEY FROM MITCH.

11:55.323 --> 11:56.541
-OKAY.
COME ON.

11:57.194 --> 11:59.109
-COME ON BABY.
-ALRIGHT BABY.

12:03.070 --> 12:03.940
[MACHINE DINGING]

12:04.071 --> 12:05.289
YES!

12:05.420 --> 12:07.988
WOO!

12:08.118 --> 12:09.250
YES!

12:12.079 --> 12:13.254
WOO.

12:29.792 --> 12:30.662
-DEALER: GOOD LUCK.

12:32.186 --> 12:33.840
25 RED.

12:33.970 --> 12:35.450
TRY AGAIN?

12:35.580 --> 12:37.147
-THAT'S IT FOR ME.

12:37.278 --> 12:38.714
-THIS IS FOR THE LADY.

12:42.152 --> 12:43.240
THAT'S FOR ME.

12:45.155 --> 12:46.766
-NO, I CAN'T LET YOU DO THAT.

12:46.896 --> 12:48.028
-I INSIST.

12:48.680 --> 12:49.812
-NO MORE BETS.

12:50.639 --> 12:52.336
-PAUL NICKELS.

12:52.467 --> 12:53.468
-DONNA MARCO.

12:53.598 --> 12:55.731
-NICE TO MEET YOU, DONNA MARCO.

13:00.170 --> 13:01.128
-DEALER: 32 RED.

13:01.868 --> 13:04.348
-32, YOU WON!

13:04.479 --> 13:05.349
-WE WON.

13:05.480 --> 13:06.829
-I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

13:07.961 --> 13:09.049
-DID YOU WIN ALL
YOUR MONEY BACK?

13:09.179 --> 13:10.180
-AND THEN SOME.

13:10.833 --> 13:12.269
-THAT'S WHAT I LIKE TO HEAR.

13:13.140 --> 13:14.097
THANK YOU.

13:14.228 --> 13:15.229
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

13:16.404 --> 13:17.579
-HOW'D YOU LIKE TO
GO SOMEPLACE QUIET,

13:17.709 --> 13:18.580
WHERE WE CAN TALK?

13:19.450 --> 13:20.843
-I'D LOVE TO.

13:25.369 --> 13:26.196
-FOR YOU.

13:26.327 --> 13:27.197
-THANK YOU.

13:35.031 --> 13:35.989
-WOULD YOU LIKE
SOMETHING TO DRINK?

13:36.119 --> 13:37.033
-SURE.

13:37.686 --> 13:38.556
-STRAWBERRY DAIQUIRI?

13:38.687 --> 13:39.862
-YEAH.

13:39.993 --> 13:41.211
-TWO STRAWBERRY
DAIQUIRIS, PLEASE.

13:41.995 --> 13:43.170
THANK YOU.

13:44.345 --> 13:46.086
SO, WHAT DO YOU DO
IN SANTA MONICA?

13:46.738 --> 13:47.870
-I'M A COUNTY LIFE GUARD.

13:48.001 --> 13:49.393
-REALLY?

13:49.524 --> 13:50.133
YOU KNOW, I ALWAYS
THOUGHT THAT WOULD BE

13:50.264 --> 13:51.439
A GREAT JOB.

13:51.569 --> 13:52.483
HANG OUT ON THE BEACH,

13:52.614 --> 13:54.094
WATCH PRETTY GIRLS GO BY.

13:54.224 --> 13:56.183
-WELL, THERE'S A LITTLE
MORE TO IT THAN THAT.

13:56.313 --> 13:57.706
-OH, I'M SURE THERE IS.

13:57.837 --> 13:58.881
THAT'S JUST THE PART
THAT APPEALS TO ME.

13:59.012 --> 14:00.491
-SO, WHAT DO YOU DO?

14:01.405 --> 14:02.450
-I'M AN IMPORTER.

14:02.580 --> 14:04.017
-OH, IMPORTER OF WHAT?

14:04.147 --> 14:06.584
-WELL, I SPECIALIZE
IN RARE JEWELS.

14:06.715 --> 14:07.934
-WOW.

14:08.064 --> 14:10.719
-IN FACT, I WAS
ADMIRING YOUR BRACELET.

14:10.850 --> 14:12.939
-OH, ITS OKAY.
-I'M SO SORRY.

14:13.069 --> 14:15.985
LET ME GET THAT FOR YOU.

14:18.770 --> 14:21.773
AS YOU CAN SEE,
I TEND TO BE VERY CLUMSY.

14:21.904 --> 14:23.514
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

14:24.820 --> 14:25.777
-OH, SORRY.

14:25.908 --> 14:27.127
I THINK THAT'S ABOUT EVERYTHING.

14:27.257 --> 14:28.345
THERE YOU GO.

14:34.395 --> 14:36.963
-YOU ARE A TERRIFIC DANCER.

14:37.746 --> 14:39.313
-FLATTERY WILL
GET YOU EVERYWHERE.

14:46.624 --> 14:47.974
HAVING A GOOD TIME SO FAR?

14:49.714 --> 14:52.369
-SO GOOD,
I'VE FORGOTTEN WHY I'M HERE.

14:53.196 --> 14:55.807
-WELL, WHAT'S THE WORST
THAT COULD HAPPEN, HUH?

14:55.938 --> 14:58.985
PETER WANTS NOTHING TO
DO WITH YOU AND ASHLEY,

14:59.115 --> 15:00.508
AND YOU COME BACK HOME.

15:00.638 --> 15:02.510
-WHERE'S HOME?

15:02.640 --> 15:04.033
I DON'T EVEN HAVE AN APARTMENT.

15:05.643 --> 15:07.994
-YOU CAN STAY WITH ME
AS LONG AS YOU WANT.

15:09.865 --> 15:13.303
-LET'S STOP TALKING
AND LET'S JUST DANCE.

15:23.400 --> 15:25.402
THANKS FOR WALKING WITH ME, TOO.

15:25.533 --> 15:27.796
-WHAT ARE FRIENDS FOR?

15:27.927 --> 15:30.364
BESIDES, ITS A
GORGEOUS NIGHT, HUH?

15:30.494 --> 15:31.931
-ITS BEAUTIFUL.

15:33.062 --> 15:34.063
[BABY CRYING]

15:34.194 --> 15:35.760
AWW, SWEETIE.

15:35.891 --> 15:37.980
-HEY, HEY, COME ON ASHLEY.

15:38.111 --> 15:39.939
-COME ON, BABY.

15:40.896 --> 15:41.679
-ITS OKAY.

15:41.810 --> 15:43.333
-ITS OKAY.

15:43.464 --> 15:45.074
AWW, ITS ALRIGHT.

15:45.205 --> 15:47.381
HEY MITCH, YOU SHOULD GET
BACK IN THERE AND DANCE.

15:47.511 --> 15:48.817
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT A FUSSY BABY.

15:48.948 --> 15:50.210
-NO, THAT'S OKAY.

15:50.340 --> 15:52.908
I COULD, I COULD
DANCE RIGHT HERE.

15:53.039 --> 15:54.388
DON'T BE SHY.
-ARE YOU SURE?

15:54.518 --> 15:55.606
-LET ME TRY, COME HERE.

15:55.737 --> 15:56.868
COME HERE, DARLING.

15:58.261 --> 16:00.960
OKAY, I GOT YOU.

16:01.090 --> 16:03.571
YEAH, YEAH.

16:03.701 --> 16:05.703
THAT'S IT GIRL, HEY.

16:05.834 --> 16:08.793
SHHH, SHHH.

16:12.580 --> 16:13.798
COME ON.

16:14.408 --> 16:15.235
-YEAH.

16:49.008 --> 16:49.791
-GOOD MORNING.

16:49.921 --> 16:51.227
-HEY, HOW YOU DOING?

16:51.358 --> 16:52.185
-NOT BAD, CONSIDERING
ASHLEY WAS UP

16:52.315 --> 16:53.142
MOST OF THE NIGHT.

16:53.273 --> 16:54.056
-OH, REALLY?

16:54.187 --> 16:55.666
HEY, ASHLEY.

16:58.539 --> 17:00.149
-ANNOUNCER: EVERYONE GOING
TO THE...

17:00.280 --> 17:05.285
[MUFFLED SPEECH]

17:05.415 --> 17:08.462
LEAVING IN 20 MINUTES,
20 MINUTES ON BUS NUMBER...

17:08.592 --> 17:10.986
[MUFFLED SPEECH]

17:35.793 --> 17:37.012
-GOOD MORNING KETCHIKAN.

17:37.143 --> 17:38.231
WILD, HUH?

17:41.756 --> 17:42.583
-HI.

17:42.713 --> 17:44.237
OH, IS THIS ASHLEY?

17:44.367 --> 17:46.630
OH, SHE IS ABSOLUTELY ADORABLE.

17:46.761 --> 17:47.849
CAN I HOLD HER?

17:47.979 --> 17:49.503
-SHE'S A LITTLE FUSSY, SO.

17:49.633 --> 17:51.635
-OH, I CAN'T WAIT
TO HAVE A BABY.

17:51.766 --> 17:52.810
-WHERE'S HOBIE?

17:52.941 --> 17:54.073
-OH, HE SHOULD BE RIGHT BACK.

17:54.203 --> 17:55.248
WE'RE GOING INTO TOWN.

17:56.075 --> 17:56.945
-HEY MITCH.

17:57.685 --> 17:58.860
I FOUND THE PERFECT
FISHING SPOT,

17:58.990 --> 18:00.383
SALMON FALLS.

18:00.514 --> 18:01.471
I ALREADY RENTED THE
GEAR, WE'RE ALL SET.

18:01.602 --> 18:02.559
-ASHLEY'S BEEN A LITTLE CRANKY,

18:02.690 --> 18:04.257
I'M GONNA HANG HERE WITH NEELY.

18:04.387 --> 18:05.649
-I THOUGHT YOU GUYS WANTED
TO GO SALMON FISHING?

18:05.780 --> 18:06.781
-MITCH, YOU KNOW,
YOU CAN GO AHEAD.

18:06.911 --> 18:08.565
WE'LL BE FINE.

18:08.696 --> 18:10.001
-YEAH, CAN'T YOU USE THAT
BABYSITTING SERVICE AGAIN?

18:10.132 --> 18:11.394
-YOU HAVE TO BOOK IN ADVANCE.

18:12.961 --> 18:15.094
-LOOK, WHY DON'T YOU TWO GO.

18:15.224 --> 18:16.617
I'LL STAY WITH ASHLEY.

18:16.747 --> 18:18.140
I'M SURE HOBIE WILL UNDERSTAND.

18:18.271 --> 18:20.099
-WELL, THANK YOU VERY
MUCH FOR THE OFFER

18:20.229 --> 18:21.622
BUT I DON'T THINK SO.

18:21.752 --> 18:22.971
-ITS OKAY, REALLY.

18:23.102 --> 18:24.233
I PRACTICALLY RAISED
MY BABY SISTER.

18:24.364 --> 18:25.713
-COME ON, MAN.

18:25.843 --> 18:27.106
THIS IS A ONCE IN
A LIFETIME OPPORTUNITY.

18:27.236 --> 18:29.934
STREAMS ARE OVERFLOWING
WITH SALMON.

18:30.065 --> 18:31.936
-ACTUALLY, I
WOULDN'T MIND GOING.

18:32.067 --> 18:33.416
IT SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

18:33.547 --> 18:34.330
-YEAH, NEELY.

18:34.461 --> 18:35.462
-YOU SURE?

18:35.592 --> 18:36.985
-ASHLEY WILL BE IN GOOD HANDS.

18:39.074 --> 18:40.467
IT'LL BE OKAY.

18:40.597 --> 18:42.382
I'LL TREAT HER LIKE
SHE WAS MY OWN.

18:42.512 --> 18:44.079
PLUS, HOBIE WILL BE
THERE TO HELP ME.

18:44.210 --> 18:45.646
-OKAY, ALRIGHT.

18:45.776 --> 18:47.300
SHE JUST HAD HER BOTTLE,
SO SHE SHOULD BE FINE.

18:47.430 --> 18:49.258
AND THERE ARE DIAPERS
IN THE STROLLER, OKAY?

18:50.607 --> 18:52.174
-SAY BYE, BYE, ASHLEY.

18:52.305 --> 18:53.393
-BYE BYE, HONEY.

18:53.523 --> 18:54.350
BYE NOW.

18:54.481 --> 18:56.004
-BYE, HAVE A GOOD TIME.

18:56.135 --> 18:57.745
-YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK
THIS IS SUCH A SMART IDEA.

18:57.875 --> 18:59.312
I REALLY DON'T.

18:59.442 --> 19:00.748
-WELL I MEAN, SHE MAY BE
A LITTLE OLD FOR HOBIE,

19:00.878 --> 19:02.489
BUT HE'S WITH HER
AND SHE'S A SWEET GIRL.

19:02.619 --> 19:03.620
-WILL YOU GUYS STOP WORRYING,

19:03.751 --> 19:04.708
THEY'RE GONNA BE FINE.

19:04.839 --> 19:06.841
BIG FISH, BIG FISH MAN, COME ON.

19:11.280 --> 19:12.151
-HOBIE.

19:12.281 --> 19:13.064
-HEY.

19:13.195 --> 19:14.065
-HI.

19:15.676 --> 19:17.504
-WHAT' S GOING ON,
HOW COME YOU HAVE ASHLEY?

19:17.634 --> 19:19.245
-I'M BABYSITTING SO
YOUR DAD AND NEELY

19:19.375 --> 19:20.637
CAN GO SALMON FISHING.

19:20.768 --> 19:21.943
-WHAT ABOUT KETCHIKAN?

19:22.073 --> 19:24.032
-WELL, YOU CAN GO BY YOURSELF.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.381
-NO, I GUESS I'LL
JUST STAY HERE THEN.

19:25.512 --> 19:26.643
-NO, DON'T BE SILLY.

19:26.774 --> 19:28.602
YOU'VE GOT TO SEE THIS TOWN,

19:28.732 --> 19:30.038
IT IS SO NEAT.

19:30.169 --> 19:31.822
GO TO CREEK STREET,
IT IS VERY COOL.

19:31.953 --> 19:33.476
-ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE
GONNA BE ALRIGHT

19:33.607 --> 19:34.695
HERE BY YOURSELF?

19:34.825 --> 19:36.349
-OF COURSE.
NOW, GO AHEAD.

19:37.350 --> 19:38.655
-ALRIGHT, I'M GONNA GO
HANG OUT WITH DONNA.

19:38.786 --> 19:39.700
-OKAY, HAVE FUN.

19:39.830 --> 19:40.614
BYE.

19:40.744 --> 19:41.789
-SEE YOU LATER.

20:00.851 --> 20:03.289
[BABY CRYING]

20:07.554 --> 20:09.164
-GAVIN IS ON THE SHIP.

20:09.860 --> 20:11.297
I DON'T KNOW HOW WE FOUND OUT.

20:11.427 --> 20:13.603
ALL I KNOW IS THAT HE'S HERE.

20:13.734 --> 20:15.475
YES, I PROMISE YOU,

20:15.605 --> 20:16.954
HE WILL NOT FIND THE EMERALDS.

20:17.085 --> 20:20.088
JUST MEET ME IN ANCHORAGE.

20:20.219 --> 20:21.132
ALRIGHT, I'LL SEE YOU THEN.

20:21.263 --> 20:26.225
[BABY CRYING]

20:39.890 --> 20:41.849
SHUT UP YOU LITTLE BRAT.

20:48.072 --> 20:50.466
-I SWEAR, IT WAS THIS BIG.

20:51.859 --> 20:54.688
-WHY IS IT WHENEVER SOMEBODY
TELLS A STORY ABOUT A FISH,

20:54.818 --> 20:56.255
ITS ALWAYS THIS BIG?

20:56.385 --> 20:58.387
-BECAUSE THAT SOMEONE
IS USUALLY A MAN,

20:58.518 --> 21:00.737
AND THEY USUALLY EXAGGERATE
ABOUT MEASUREMENTS.

21:00.868 --> 21:03.131
-HEY CODY, YOU THINK SHE'S
TRYING TO TELL ME SOMETHING?

21:05.089 --> 21:07.178
-OH MY GOSH, YOU GUYS,

21:07.309 --> 21:08.745
LOOK AT HOW BEAUTIFUL.

21:10.486 --> 21:12.227
-SHIP SAILS FOR JUNEAU
IN FIVE HOURS.

21:12.358 --> 21:14.055
-I SAY, LET'S NOT WASTE
ANOTHER MINUTE, HUH?

21:14.185 --> 21:14.969
-LET'S DO IT.

21:15.099 --> 21:16.492
-ALRIGHT YOU GUYS,

21:16.623 --> 21:17.667
I'M GONNA STAY HERE
AND TAKE SOME PICTURES.

21:17.798 --> 21:18.668
-BE CAREFUL, HUH?

21:18.799 --> 21:19.713
-OKAY, HAVE FUN.

21:19.843 --> 21:20.583
-OKAY, THANKS, SEE YA.

21:20.714 --> 21:21.584
-BYE.

21:22.193 --> 21:24.108
-I SENSE THE BIG FISH.

21:41.909 --> 21:44.259
-GOD, THIS IS AMAZING.

21:57.054 --> 22:01.320
[HEAVY BREATHING]

22:02.799 --> 22:06.020
[GROWLING]

22:08.718 --> 22:10.024
OH MY GOD!

22:11.068 --> 22:12.069
OH MY!

22:13.941 --> 22:15.246
OH MY GOD!

22:15.377 --> 22:16.422
HELP!

22:16.987 --> 22:17.858
MITCH!

22:19.033 --> 22:20.861
OH MY GOD!

22:58.681 --> 22:59.813
[MUFFLED SPEECH]

22:59.943 --> 23:00.857
-WOAH.

23:02.642 --> 23:03.599
HEY, MAN.
-YEAH, MAN.

23:03.730 --> 23:05.340
WOO!

23:05.471 --> 23:07.951
-COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON.

23:08.082 --> 23:09.083
-WOO!

23:10.345 --> 23:11.825
-WOO! LOOK AT THAT BABY.

23:13.609 --> 23:14.784
-HELP!

23:14.915 --> 23:16.090
MITCH!

23:16.743 --> 23:17.526
MITCH!

23:19.833 --> 23:20.834
MITCH!

23:20.964 --> 23:22.270
CODY!

23:23.837 --> 23:24.925
-COME ON.

24:17.978 --> 24:19.719
-GOD.

24:20.589 --> 24:21.460
-MITCH!

24:21.590 --> 24:22.896
HURRY!

24:24.027 --> 24:25.246
-HANG IN THERE.

24:25.376 --> 24:26.682
HEY, GET OUT.

24:27.596 --> 24:28.467
GET OUT.

24:29.729 --> 24:31.992
SEE IF YOU CAN FIND SOMETHING
TO DISTRACT THIS THING WITH.

24:32.775 --> 24:34.298
HANG IN THERE NEELY.

24:35.212 --> 24:36.518
GO ON.

24:42.524 --> 24:43.743
-MITCH!

24:43.873 --> 24:44.961
-MITCH.

24:46.093 --> 24:46.963
-MITCH!

24:48.704 --> 24:49.836
-GET OUTTA HERE.

24:49.966 --> 24:51.490
GO ON.

25:00.499 --> 25:01.543
-MITCH!

25:01.674 --> 25:02.588
MITCH!

25:02.718 --> 25:04.372
-GET OUTTA HERE, GET OUT.

25:15.862 --> 25:16.906
GET OUTTA HERE.

25:17.037 --> 25:18.342
-GET OUT!

25:18.473 --> 25:20.693
GET OUTTA THERE!

25:25.872 --> 25:27.221
GO ON.

25:28.222 --> 25:29.528
-OH THANK GOD.

25:30.224 --> 25:31.530
-YOU OKAY?

25:31.660 --> 25:34.054
-YEAH OTHER THAN
CAUGHT UNDER THIS LOG.

25:34.184 --> 25:35.664
-OKAY, ON THREE,

25:35.795 --> 25:36.752
ONE, TWO, THREE.

25:40.626 --> 25:42.366
SEE IF YOU CAN FIND SOMETHING
TO LEVERAGE HER OUTTA HERE.

25:42.497 --> 25:43.454
-ALRIGHT.

25:43.585 --> 25:45.239
-ALRIGHT, JUST TAKE IT EASY.

25:45.369 --> 25:46.196
ALRIGHT.

25:46.327 --> 25:47.110
YOU SURE YOU'RE OKAY?

25:47.241 --> 25:48.372
-I'M REALLY COLD.

25:48.503 --> 25:50.505
I CAN'T FEEL MY LEGS.

25:50.636 --> 25:52.376
-ALRIGHT, WE'RE GONNA
GET YOU OUTTA HERE.

25:52.507 --> 25:53.900
-I KNOW THAT.

25:54.030 --> 25:55.162
I KNOW.

25:55.292 --> 25:56.859
-DID I EVER TELL YOU THE TIME

25:56.990 --> 25:58.905
EDDY KRAMER WAS TRAPPED,

25:59.035 --> 26:00.559
PINNED UNDERNEATH THE VAULT,

26:00.689 --> 26:02.430
INSIDE AN ARMORED CAR?

26:02.561 --> 26:04.040
-YEAH.
-SINKING TO THE
BOTTOM OF THE OCEAN,

26:04.171 --> 26:05.041
DID I EVER TELL YOU ABOUT THAT?

26:05.172 --> 26:06.260
-YEAH, ABOUT TEN TIMES.

26:06.390 --> 26:07.783
-I THOUGHT I DID.

26:07.914 --> 26:10.525
DO I EVER MENTION
THAT HE GOT OUT OKAY?

26:15.443 --> 26:18.620
-MITCH, I'M REALLY,
REALLY SCARRED, ASHLEY.

26:18.751 --> 26:21.057
-ASHLEY IS GONNA HAVE A MOMMY

26:21.188 --> 26:22.929
TO TUCK HER INTO TONIGHT,
I GUARANTEE IT.

26:23.059 --> 26:24.234
COME ON CODY!

26:24.365 --> 26:25.627
-HERE YOU GO.

26:26.454 --> 26:28.543
JUST GOTTA POSITION
IT AS A FULCRUM.

26:28.674 --> 26:29.675
-YOU OKAY?
-YEAH.

26:29.805 --> 26:31.024
-ALRIGHT, HERE YOU GO.

26:31.154 --> 26:32.460
-READY?

26:32.591 --> 26:34.505
-ONE, TWO THREE.

26:39.685 --> 26:40.773
SHE'S FREE.

26:42.818 --> 26:44.428
-I'M SO COLD.

26:52.219 --> 26:53.612
GET ME OUT OF HERE.

26:53.742 --> 26:54.961
I'M SO COLD.

26:55.091 --> 26:55.962
-WE'LL GET YOU
BACK TO THE SHIP.

26:56.092 --> 26:56.876
GET YOU SOME BLANKETS.

26:57.006 --> 26:58.399
IT'S ALRIGHT.

26:59.226 --> 27:00.619
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

27:09.192 --> 27:10.063
-HERE YOU GO.

27:10.193 --> 27:11.630
-THANKS.

27:11.760 --> 27:13.066
LOOK, WHY DON'T YOU
GET SOME REST, HUH?

27:13.196 --> 27:14.415
AND I'LL TAKE ASHLEY
BACK TO YOUR ROOM.

27:14.545 --> 27:16.417
-OH, NO, NO,
I WANT HER TO STAY.

27:16.547 --> 27:19.681
YOU KNOW, THERE FOR A MINUTE,

27:19.812 --> 27:21.117
I DIDN'T THINK
I WAS GONNA SEE HER AGAIN.

27:21.857 --> 27:23.729
I MEAN, ALL I KEPT THINKING WAS,

27:23.859 --> 27:25.731
WHO'S GONNA TAKE CARE OF HER?

27:27.167 --> 27:28.516
AND THEN I LOOKED UP,

27:29.169 --> 27:32.520
AND I SAW YOU, SAVING ME.

27:33.564 --> 27:35.131
THANK YOU.

27:46.273 --> 27:49.711
-I, I'LL GO GET THE

27:50.320 --> 27:51.539
-DIAPER BAG.

27:52.758 --> 27:53.933
THANKS.

28:10.079 --> 28:10.863
-HEY YOU.

28:10.993 --> 28:12.212
-MITCH, HEY.

28:12.342 --> 28:13.430
LISTEN,
I JUST HEARD WHAT HAPPENED.

28:13.561 --> 28:14.344
IS NEELY OKAY?

28:14.475 --> 28:15.737
-YEAH, YEAH, SHE'S FINE.

28:15.868 --> 28:17.043
SHE'S UP ON THE DECK,
LYING DOWN,

28:17.173 --> 28:18.392
I JUST WENT TO GET
THE DIAPER BAG.

28:20.263 --> 28:21.830
-HOLD ON, I'LL GO WITH YA.

28:22.657 --> 28:24.137
YOU KNOW, IT SOUNDED
LIKE A REALLY CLOSE CALL.

28:24.267 --> 28:25.094
-YEAH, IT WAS.

28:25.225 --> 28:26.313
IS THIS YOUR ROOM?

28:26.966 --> 28:27.793
-YES, WHY?

28:27.923 --> 28:29.446
-DID YOU SWITCH CABINS?

28:29.577 --> 28:31.448
-NO, I'VE BEEN
HERE THE WHOLE TIME.

28:32.058 --> 28:34.147
-DONNA, I SAW A GUY GO
IN YOUR ROOM THIS MORNING,

28:34.277 --> 28:35.714
HE HAD THE KEY.

28:35.844 --> 28:36.932
-ARE YOU SURE IT WASN'T
ONE OF THE STUARTS?

28:37.063 --> 28:38.368
-UH, YEAH.

28:38.499 --> 28:40.327
HE WAS TALL, DARK,
AND HAD A GOATEE.

28:41.197 --> 28:42.808
-NO WONDER I CAN'T FIND MY KEY.

28:42.938 --> 28:44.461
MUST OF TAKEN IT WHEN
HE KNOCKED MY PURSE

28:44.592 --> 28:45.549
OUT OF MY HANDS.

28:46.159 --> 28:47.029
WHY WOULD HE DO THAT?

28:47.160 --> 28:48.639
-WHO IS THIS GUY ANYWAY?

28:48.770 --> 28:50.206
-HIS NAME'S PAUL NICKELS,

28:50.337 --> 28:51.817
HE'S A JEWELRY
IMPORTER FROM DULUTH.

28:53.601 --> 28:55.124
-HERE YOU ARE MA'AM,

28:55.255 --> 28:56.647
THAT'S TWO TICKETS FOR
THE HELICOPTER TRIP IN SKAGWAY.

28:56.778 --> 28:58.475
-OH THANK YOU,
WE'RE HAVIN' A GREAT TIME.

28:58.606 --> 28:59.563
BEAUTIFUL SHIP.

28:59.694 --> 29:01.217
-THANK YOU, ENJOY YOUR DAY.

29:07.441 --> 29:08.442
-EXCUSE ME,

29:08.572 --> 29:09.356
DO YOU HAVE A MAP OF JUNEAU?

29:09.486 --> 29:10.749
-YES MA'AM, ONE MOMENT.

29:12.359 --> 29:13.229
OH, THERE YOU ARE MA'AM.

29:13.360 --> 29:14.448
-THANK YOU.

29:14.578 --> 29:15.841
-YOU'RE WELCOME,
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

29:24.371 --> 29:25.981
-HEY, WHAT'S UP?

29:26.112 --> 29:27.591
-HEY HOBIE,
I'M JUST CHECKING OUT

29:27.722 --> 29:29.463
WHAT THERE IS TO DO
AT THE NEXT STOP.

29:29.593 --> 29:32.727
-OH, IN JUNEAU, THE GLACIERS'
SUPPOSED TO BE UNREAL.

29:32.858 --> 29:35.121
I HEARD YOU CAN GO PARAGLIDING
FROM THE MENDENHALL GLACIER

29:35.251 --> 29:36.513
BACK DOWN TO THE SHIP.

29:37.340 --> 29:38.777
ITS SUPPOSED TO BE INCREDIBLE.

29:38.907 --> 29:40.822
HAVE YOU EVER BEEN
PARAGLIDING, CLAIR?

29:42.128 --> 29:43.912
-WHAT? NO.

29:44.043 --> 29:45.000
NO, NEVER.

29:45.740 --> 29:46.697
BUT I'D LOVE TO LEARN.

29:46.828 --> 29:47.611
LET'S GO.

29:47.742 --> 29:48.787
-KILLER.

29:52.312 --> 29:54.096
-SURE YOU DON'T WANT ME
TO COME WITH YOU?

29:54.227 --> 29:56.011
-ALWAYS THERE TO BACK ME UP.

29:56.142 --> 29:58.013
-IT'S WHAT LIFEGUARDS DO.

29:58.144 --> 30:00.189
-REMEMBER,
THIS IS YOUR VACATION.

30:00.320 --> 30:02.409
-RIGHT, THAT SORT OF IS.

30:04.846 --> 30:06.805
-I JUST HOPE I'M
DOING THE RIGHT THING.

30:09.546 --> 30:12.071
-I JUST HOPE PETER
LIKES SURPRISES.

30:13.986 --> 30:15.161
OH COME ON, I'LL WALK YOU DOWN.

30:15.291 --> 30:16.815
-THANKS.

31:12.827 --> 31:14.350
-HEY, COME ON.

31:36.633 --> 31:38.200
-HI, LESLIE.

31:38.809 --> 31:41.812
I WANT MY EMERALDS
AND I WANT THEM NOW.

31:43.553 --> 31:45.164
-THEY'RE IN MY SUITE.

32:05.575 --> 32:06.446
-OPEN IT.

32:07.055 --> 32:07.926
OPEN IT.

32:11.059 --> 32:11.842
-WON'T GO.

32:11.973 --> 32:13.366
-GET OVER HERE.

32:17.152 --> 32:18.588
COME ON.

32:20.416 --> 32:21.548
-CLAIR, WHAT'S GOING ON?

32:23.245 --> 32:24.377
CLAIR, HOLD IT.

32:24.986 --> 32:26.248
WAIT A MINUTE, CLAIR, STOP.

32:26.379 --> 32:27.684
WHO IS THIS GUY?

32:36.737 --> 32:37.738
-HEY MAN, WHAT'S GOING ON?

32:38.913 --> 32:40.567
OH, WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

32:40.697 --> 32:41.524
YOU OKAY?

32:41.655 --> 32:42.917
-NEVER HAD A BETTER DAY.

32:43.787 --> 32:45.920
-SORRY, THERE'S NO ONE
REGISTERED UNDER THAT NAME.

32:47.313 --> 32:50.577
-WELL SHE'S IN ROOM B 422.

32:51.230 --> 32:52.405
-WHAT'S THIS ALL ABOUT?

32:52.535 --> 32:53.928
-I'M NOT SURE YET, HANG ON.

32:54.059 --> 32:56.583
-THAT ROOM'S OCCUPIED BY
MS. LESLIE STRYKER,

32:56.713 --> 32:58.498
AT LEAST THAT'S THE
NAME ON THE PASSPORT.

32:58.628 --> 33:00.195
-LESLIE STRYKER?

33:00.326 --> 33:01.762
WHAT THE HELL'S GOIN' ON?

33:02.893 --> 33:03.938
THANK YOU CAPTAIN.

33:04.895 --> 33:06.636
WHO IS LESLIE STRYKER.

33:06.767 --> 33:08.334
I GOTTA FIND HOBIE.

33:14.688 --> 33:16.342
-OKAY, WORK TO RICO,

33:16.472 --> 33:17.647
RIGHT AT THE CAMERA,
RIGHT AT THE CAMERA.

33:17.778 --> 33:19.040
OKAY.

33:19.171 --> 33:21.216
BIG EYES, NICE,
BEAUTIFUL, BEAUTIFUL.

33:21.347 --> 33:22.565
NOW OFF CAMERA.

33:22.696 --> 33:23.958
THAT'S GREAT.

33:33.446 --> 33:34.795
-COME HERE, SWEETIE.

33:34.925 --> 33:36.318
LET'S FEED YOU
BEFORE YOU MEET YOUR DADDY.

33:36.449 --> 33:37.450
COME ON.

33:37.580 --> 33:39.408
-BACK ON CAMERA, NICE, NICE.

33:39.539 --> 33:40.801
YOU'RE WORKING WELL TOGETHER.

33:40.931 --> 33:41.758
THAT'S TERRIFIC.

33:41.889 --> 33:43.325
VERY GOOD, VERY NICE.

33:43.456 --> 33:44.457
NOW, LET'S SEE,

33:44.587 --> 33:45.675
EVERYBODY TURN RIGHT, PLEASE.

33:45.806 --> 33:47.503
-STOP TELLING ME TO CALM DOWN,

33:47.634 --> 33:48.852
HE'S FOUND ME.

33:49.462 --> 33:51.464
HE DOESN'T HAVE
THE EMERALDS, I DO.

33:52.552 --> 33:54.771
THAT IS, IF I CAN GET TO THEM.

33:55.598 --> 33:58.906
NO, NEVER MIND,
I DON'T HAVE TIME TO EXPLAIN.

33:59.037 --> 34:01.561
JUST MEET ME IN
A TOWN CALLED CICELY.

34:01.691 --> 34:04.303
IT'S DUE EAST OF
MENDENHALL GLACIER.

34:05.086 --> 34:06.174
RIGHT.

34:06.740 --> 34:08.219
OH, DON'T WORRY ABOUT HOW
I'M GONNA GET THERE,

34:08.350 --> 34:09.482
JUST BE THERE.

34:10.135 --> 34:12.092
OKAY, BYE.

34:25.106 --> 34:27.065
-REALLY NICE, REALLY NICE GIRLS.

34:27.195 --> 34:29.241
OKAY, NOW BACK ON THE CAMERA.

34:29.371 --> 34:30.371
GOOD.

34:30.503 --> 34:32.766
SHOULDERS BACK, VERY NICE.

34:32.896 --> 34:34.942
NOW THIS WAY, RIGHT OVER HERE.

34:35.072 --> 34:36.204
LOOK HERE, HERE'S YOUR FOCUS,
RIGHT HERE.

34:36.335 --> 34:37.684
OVER ON THAT LEFT.

34:37.813 --> 34:39.641
FOCUS LEFT, GOOD, BEAUTIFUL.

34:39.773 --> 34:42.036
GOOD, BIG EYES, BIG EYES,

34:42.167 --> 34:43.168
BIG SMILE.

34:43.297 --> 34:44.821
SUPER, OKAY, LET'S WRAP IT UP.

34:44.952 --> 34:46.214
THE NEXT SHOOT'S IN JUNEAU.

34:47.868 --> 34:49.348
NICE JOB.

34:49.478 --> 34:50.739
BEAUTIFUL.

34:50.871 --> 34:52.306
ITS GONNA BE AWESOME.

34:55.005 --> 34:57.007
-SHE IS SO BEAUTIFUL.

34:57.138 --> 34:58.444
-THANKS.

34:58.574 --> 34:59.401
-LISTEN, GOOD LUCK
WITH PETER, OKAY?

34:59.532 --> 35:00.576
-THANK YOU, I NEED IT.

35:00.707 --> 35:01.925
HAVE FUN IN TOWN.
-BYE.

35:02.056 --> 35:02.709
-YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.
-THANK YOU.

35:23.730 --> 35:24.687
-HOBIE.

35:24.818 --> 35:25.993
-WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

35:26.124 --> 35:27.473
WE'RE JUST ABOUT
TO DOCK IN JUNEAU,

35:27.603 --> 35:28.996
I THOUGHT YOU WANTED
TO BE FIRST ON THE TRAM?

35:29.127 --> 35:30.345
-I KNOW, I'M SORRY.

35:30.476 --> 35:32.217
I JUST, I GOT A
REALLY BAD HEADACHE.

35:32.347 --> 35:33.131
-ARE YOU GONNA BE ALRIGHT?

35:33.261 --> 35:34.219
-YEAH, I'M OKAY.

35:34.349 --> 35:35.655
COME ON, LET'S GO.

35:36.917 --> 35:38.701
COME ON HOBIE.

35:38.832 --> 35:40.138
-I'M RIGHT BEHIND YOU.

35:57.851 --> 35:59.287
-HURRY UP, WE'LL MISS THE TRAM.

36:02.421 --> 36:03.770
COME ON.

36:06.947 --> 36:08.340
-GET OUTTA MY WAY.

36:12.822 --> 36:13.606
-HEY THERE, SWEETIE.

36:13.736 --> 36:15.042
YOU READY TO GO?

36:16.130 --> 36:17.044
-THERE YOU GO.

36:19.394 --> 36:20.700
YOU HAVE A NICE DAY.

36:24.878 --> 36:26.401
-HERE WE GO, SWEETIE.

36:26.532 --> 36:27.576
OKAY.

36:40.154 --> 36:41.199
-COME ON.

36:51.296 --> 36:52.166
-TICKETS PLEASE.

36:52.688 --> 36:53.515
TICKETS PLEASE.

36:55.038 --> 36:56.562
TICKETS PLEASE, THANK YOU.

36:58.346 --> 36:59.173
-HEY.

36:59.826 --> 37:01.262
-HEY, HEY, WAIT.

37:04.091 --> 37:05.440
-HEY, WATCH IT PAL.

37:05.962 --> 37:07.268
-THIS WILL WORK REALLY WELL.

37:09.096 --> 37:10.750
-TICKET LINE FIRST, PLEASE.

37:11.446 --> 37:12.360
-HEY.

37:20.238 --> 37:21.804
-ITS ALRIGHT, HERE YOU GO.

37:21.935 --> 37:23.545
DO YOU HAVE ANY MORE?

37:23.676 --> 37:25.286
-LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
THE TRAM IS NOW DEPARTING.

37:25.417 --> 37:26.896
PLEASE STAND CLEAR OF THE DOORS

37:27.027 --> 37:27.941
AND ENJOY THE RIDE.

37:28.071 --> 37:29.159
-ITS ALRIGHT, HERE YOU GO.

37:31.466 --> 37:32.641
-HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

37:32.772 --> 37:34.077
YOU GOTTA PAY FOR THAT TICKET.

37:38.212 --> 37:39.518
-HERE.

37:46.873 --> 37:48.875
HOW LONG 'TILL
THE NEXT TRAM LEAVES?

37:49.005 --> 37:50.442
-THERE'S ONLY ONE TRAM,

37:50.572 --> 37:53.314
IT TAKES 20 MINUTES TO
GO UP AND COME DOWN.

37:54.663 --> 37:56.230
-IS THERE ANY OTHER WAY
BACK DOWN?

37:57.057 --> 37:58.319
-ONLY IF YOU WANNA PARAGLIDE.

38:10.375 --> 38:12.333
-WOW, LOOK AT THAT VIEW.

38:15.858 --> 38:18.426
WELL, I'VE DONE A LOT OF
HANG GLIDING BACK HOME.

38:21.560 --> 38:23.779
PARASAILING SHOULDN'T
BE THAT MUCH DIFFERENT.

38:27.740 --> 38:28.784
-ANNOUNCER: TO BE CONTINUED.

38:28.915 --> 38:30.003
-THIS WAY HONEY, LOOK IT.

38:41.188 --> 38:46.280
-♪ [END THEME PLAYING]
